{
  "text": "This subsection explains the general framework of the approach known as the majorization-minimization algorithm [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Let \u03b8 be a set of objective variables, e.g., \u03b8 = {T, V} in the case of NMF (19) . For an objective function C(\u03b8 ), an auxiliary function C + (\u03b8 ,\u03b8) with a set of auxiliary variables\u03b8 satisfies the following two conditions.",
